#Text=Become an Internet Master
#Text=A new common culture is arising from the increasingly ubiquitousness of technology in our everyday lives .
#Text=It became really relevant part of communication and spreading of trend .
#Text=If you are new to this it can be really difficult to understand because often a stratification of layer of meaning or has to be seen as very ironic/ post-ironic critic .
#Text=Here 's a little step by step guide into the Internet Culture .
#Text=Steps
#Text=Browse 4chan.4chan is an image board where you can post anonymously .
#Text=Since it is a community you have to learn and respect the rules , if you do n’t like them you can go to a similar website like 8 chan or other image board like reddit , imgur or 9gag .
#Text=The member of the community usually refers to each other using the term /b/ros .
#Text=There ’s a specific language that you should learn in order to get along with the other users .
#Text=The website is divided into different categories depending on the topic , learning the difference between each boards can be very useful .
#Text=Users can open a thread about a certain issue , each thread is identified by an automatically random generated number .
#Text=There are some moderators that can ban you if your comments or threads are inappropriate , but basically it does n’t have really strict censorship rules like Facebook or Instagram .
#Text=Get into a weird Facebook group .

#Text=Weird Facebook , or Post-Ironic Facebook is a loose agglomeration of Facebook pages , also known as “ Meme Pages , ” that create and distribute dank memes , often along a certain theme or topic .
#Text=Many of these pages have become popular both because of their absurd humor , but also because of possible advantages given to the “ Page ” format in the Facebook algorithm .
#Text=If you get into the group you can follow the spreading process of viral content and you can be aware of the meaning of what you see on your Facebook home .
#Text=Drown in Deep Web .
#Text=The deep web , invisible web , or hidden web are parts of the World Wide Web whose contents are not indexed by standard search engines for any reason .
#Text=To surf the deep web you ’ll need a specific browser called Tor .
#Text=The deep web includes many very common uses such as web mail , online banking but also paid for services with a paywall such as video on demand , and many more .
#Text=But of course is also the place where a lot of illegal activities take place .
#Text=You can buy drugs ( on Silkroad that was a kind of ebay for illegal substances ) , weapons , fake documents , hacking services and datas , but it was also used by terrorists to keep in touch .
#Text=To buy on the deep web you ’ll need Bitcoin , a cryptocurrency and a payment system invented by an unidentified programmer , or group of programmers , under the name of Satoshi Nakamoto .
#Text=For its elitarian nature deep web was chosen to reach an alternative public rather than the surface web .

#Text=A lot of indie-alternative games are only available there ( Sad Satan is the most famous ) and also a popular experimental music group , called Death Grips choose the deep web for the release of one of their album “ No Love Deep Web ” .
#Text=Scroll Tumblr .
#Text=Tumblr is a blogging social network .
#Text=When you register you automatically create your own blog .
#Text=There you can post your own contents or reblog other people .
#Text=You can have many blogs from one profile and dedicate each blog to a specific topic .
#Text=Tumblr is mostly used by teenager
#Text=this explains the large amount of porn and self harm/suicidal content .
#Text=It ’s a kind of journal but mostly composed from images , through which you share your own aesthetic .
#Text=The more you get followers , likes and got reblogged the more you become popular on tumblr .
#Text=The most popular tumblr has actually reached 100 000 followers and is kept from a 16 year old girl .
#Text=Tumblr has a really precise aesthetic and was for a long time the cradle of a lot of artistic currents on the internet like tumblr-core , sea punk , vaporwave , health goth , sad boys etc ...
#Text=Sleep deprivation is good .
#Text=To proficiency into becoming a master of the internet
#Text=the best thing is to sleep not more than 4 hours a night .
#Text=If you think going out can distract you form the real joy of becoming an Internet master
#Text=avoid any social contact outside , except convention where the main topic is Internet or any subculture related .
#Text=Buy sugary soft drink or energy drink and junk food so you wo n’t need to waste time in cooking .
#Text=Get into online gaming , became a moderator of a forum and find your own community on the internet .
#Text=Praise Kek .

#Text=The Cult of Kek , also known as the Church of Kek , is a satirical religion based around the worship of the ancient Egyptian deity Kek ( also spelled Kuk or Keku ) , an androgynous God of darkness and chaos who is often depicted as a frog or frog-headed man in male form or a snake-headed woman in female form .

#Text=On 4chan , the character Pepe the Frog is often considered a modern avatar of the diety , who uses ancient Egyptian meme magic to influence the world , often by fulfilling the wishes of posts that end in repeating numbers .
#Text=Additionally , the deity is often associated with the popular 4chan slang term “ Kek ” , and is often embraced by supporters of 2016 Republican presidential candidate Donald Trump .
#Text=Practitioners are known to frequently write “ praise Kek , ” and jokingly refer to the church as a “ religion of peace . ”
